From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fujisan Developer <fujisan@atari>
Date: Mon, 3 Mar 2025 00:00:00 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] Replace netsio_cold_reset with netsio_warm_reset in Atari800_Coldstart

Atari800_Coldstart() is called from many paths inside the atari800 core:
BINLOAD_Loader(), MEMORY_InitialiseMachine(), libatari800_reboot_with_file(),
cartridge changes, and more. In all of these cases, the original
netsio_cold_reset(0xFF) triggered a full FujiNet-PC process restart via
fnSystem.reboot() -- causing SIGABRT crashes when FujiNet-PC was in the
middle of a SIO exchange and the emulator cold-reset underneath it.

The correct fix is to replace netsio_cold_reset(0xFF) with
netsio_warm_reset(0xFE). A warm reset tells FujiNet-PC to reset its SIO
state machine (boot_config, status_wait_count, pending transactions) without
restarting the process. This is safe and appropriate for every internal
cold start path:

  - BINLOAD_Loader(): emulator reboots to run the XEX bootloader. FujiNet-PC
    needs to reset its SIO state to track the new boot sequence, but the
    process must keep running for N: and other network devices.
  - MEMORY_InitialiseMachine(): called during emulator (re)init. Same logic.
  - cartridge swap, system.restart, etc.: same.

Fujisan's explicit coldBoot() is unchanged -- it still sends
netsio_cold_reset(0xFF) first, waits up to 3 seconds for FujiNet-PC to
restart and reconnect, and then calls Atari800_Coldstart(). The subsequent
netsio_warm_reset(0xFE) from Atari800_Coldstart() arrives after FujiNet-PC
has already restarted and is harmless.

Atari800_Warmstart() already sends netsio_warm_reset(0xFE) and works
correctly. Atari800_Coldstart() should do the same.
---
 src/atari.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/atari.c b/src/atari.c
index cef0c10f..d3a4b7c1 100644
--- a/src/atari.c
+++ b/src/atari.c
@@ -278,7 +278,7 @@ void Atari800_Coldstart(void)
 	}
 #endif
 #ifdef NETSIO
-	if(netsio_enabled)
-		netsio_cold_reset();
+	if (netsio_enabled)
+		netsio_warm_reset();
 #endif /* NETSIO */
 }
 
